item.title: About Jake
item.description: Jake Lee [he/him] wants to protect the redwood forests. He is an engineer, maker, artist, and aspiring farmer. Knowledge is powerful, but so is convenience. He is frustrated by the current agricultural system in America (and globally). Equal access to education for all people is important to him. Jake hopes to some day combine all of his frustrations with his interest in robotics to build tools that can simultaneously help small farmers and provide engineering education to rural communities.
